1
00:00:02,033 --> 00:00:02,933
this is it

2
00:00:03,333 --> 00:00:05,866
your power has grown to preposterous levels

3
00:00:06,200 --> 00:00:08,066
your chemical storage is overflowing

4
00:00:08,833 --> 00:00:11,200
your blast furnace has been running for days

5
00:00:11,866 --> 00:00:13,666
you're swimming in stainless steel

6
00:00:14,066 --> 00:00:16,733
but now you need to become multi-planetary

7
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:19,866
the vacuum of space is lethal to the unprepared

8
00:00:20,833 --> 00:00:21,866
but that's why you're here

9
00:00:22,066 --> 00:00:23,433
it's time for the home stretch

10
00:00:23,666 --> 00:00:25,333
you're on the precipice of the midgame

11
00:00:25,733 --> 00:00:27,500
ready to move on from this beginner stuff

12
00:00:27,833 --> 00:00:30,000
so today we go to space

13
00:00:30,233 --> 00:00:31,833
this is episode 8

14
00:00:32,133 --> 00:00:32,933
HV

15
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:35,633
to infinity and beyond

16
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:50,300
MV was a pretty straight line

17
00:00:50,533 --> 00:00:52,200
a nice little self-contained chapter

18
00:00:52,633 --> 00:00:54,133
HV is the opposite

19
00:00:54,466 --> 00:00:56,833
you're gonna be jumping around in the quest book quite a bit

20
00:00:57,500 --> 00:00:59,100
you should have the habits down by now

21
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:01,000
so start with the you're gonna hate this quests

22
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:02,200
just a reminder

23
00:01:02,233 --> 00:01:04,500
in every tier you'll have a bunch of new stuff to do

24
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:06,433
but also some of the same stuff every time

25
00:01:08,200 --> 00:01:09,400
make machine parts

26
00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:11,100
upgrade machines

27
00:01:11,333 --> 00:01:12,700
make energy hatches

28
00:01:12,866 --> 00:01:13,800
make coils

29
00:01:14,133 --> 00:01:15,100
make plastics

30
00:01:15,633 --> 00:01:17,100
and improve circuits

31
00:01:17,433 --> 00:01:18,900
sometimes the order is varied up

32
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:21,066
sometimes you can put things off for a long time

33
00:01:21,266 --> 00:01:23,066
but eventually you'll do it all

34
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:25,600
assuming you have all the stainless steel you need

35
00:01:25,600 --> 00:01:27,200
and don't forget about mining the basics

36
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:28,466
especially copper

37
00:01:28,733 --> 00:01:30,633
nothing's really stopping you from going straight at it

38
00:01:31,133 --> 00:01:32,833
you can get the MV circuit assembler right away

39
00:01:32,833 --> 00:01:34,266
and start making circuits faster

40
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:37,200
you won't be able to make any of the new circuits until you get the clean room though

41
00:01:37,466 --> 00:01:38,300
we'll get to that

42
00:01:38,466 --> 00:01:40,000
for now take advantage of the speed

43
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,633
and grab some important upgrades

44
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:45,133
the HV miners are super worth having

45
00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:48,033
and the last stop before you can get into the multi block mining rigs

46
00:01:48,133 --> 00:01:49,100
grab 3 or 4

47
00:01:49,100 --> 00:01:51,666
and keep them running on everything all the time

48
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:53,333
and grab compressed chests too

49
00:01:53,666 --> 00:01:54,466
they're pricey

50
00:01:54,466 --> 00:01:56,066
but they keep their inventory when broken

51
00:01:56,066 --> 00:01:58,933
so this is a massive upgrade for your mining process

52
00:01:59,466 --> 00:02:01,666
HV machines also add an output slot

53
00:02:01,666 --> 00:02:05,300
so you can start getting byproduct bonus outputs from various ore processing stages

54
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:07,466
not every byproduct is worth having

55
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:08,933
some just gum up the works

56
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:13,033
so filtering and fully automating processing at this point can be awkward if you don't know some magic

57
00:02:13,066 --> 00:02:16,033
with a couple of macerators, ore washers and centrifuges

58
00:02:16,033 --> 00:02:17,933
you can stay loaded with resources

59
00:02:18,233 --> 00:02:20,500
copper especially is nice for all the bonus gold

60
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:22,500
but tons of stuff is worth running through

61
00:02:22,700 --> 00:02:24,300
starting your nickel through the macerator

62
00:02:24,300 --> 00:02:26,066
then sending it through a chemical bath with mercury

63
00:02:26,066 --> 00:02:28,200
will net you a fair amount of early platinum too

64
00:02:28,900 --> 00:02:30,866
you should upgrade all your workshop machines

65
00:02:30,866 --> 00:02:33,000
but until your passive setups for chemicals and silicone and everything else you set up are too slow

66
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:34,933
（向上合并）

67
00:02:34,933 --> 00:02:36,300
there's no need to upgrade those

68
00:02:36,333 --> 00:02:39,033
you'll just run into a power crunch sooner than you otherwise would have

69
00:02:39,266 --> 00:02:39,733
at this point

70
00:02:39,733 --> 00:02:43,733
the main things that are going to be eating power are the EBF and the ore processing line you just set up

71
00:02:44,133 --> 00:02:46,000
use all the fuel you have keeping those going

72
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,900
and if you have extra, power your workshop

73
00:02:48,233 --> 00:02:50,866
if not, this is a good time to make use of your old steam infrastructure

74
00:02:50,866 --> 00:02:53,733
and send a drip of power to a battery for your hand use machines

75
00:02:54,300 --> 00:02:57,333
having to wait for batteries to charge to use single blocks is a little annoying

76
00:02:57,333 --> 00:03:01,200
but losing time redoing failed smelting operations in the EBF is worse

77
00:03:01,633 --> 00:03:03,500
if you find yourself waiting more than you can stand

78
00:03:03,500 --> 00:03:05,200
it's time to scale up your power production

79
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:06,633
if your power is holding up well

80
00:03:06,633 --> 00:03:07,933
skip ahead to the clean room

81
00:03:08,033 --> 00:03:09,866
but you'll want to hear what's next either way

82
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,266
if you went oil for power

83
00:03:12,266 --> 00:03:13,700
and frankly, even if you didn't

84
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:15,400
you might want to think about an oil drilling rig

85
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,700
and some long distance piping

86
00:03:17,233 --> 00:03:18,500
use your prospector on bedrock

87
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:20,233
and find a fluid pool of regular oil

88
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:22,133
the underground pools are giant

89
00:03:22,133 --> 00:03:24,400
so you should be safe to pump here for a long while

90
00:03:24,866 --> 00:03:26,300
pop down the multi block oil rig

91
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:28,033
attach a long distance pipe input

92
00:03:28,033 --> 00:03:28,866
load the chunk

93
00:03:28,900 --> 00:03:31,100
and place pipes down until you get back to your base

94
00:03:32,266 --> 00:03:33,500
and when you get back

95
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:35,500
send the oil into your new distillation tower

96
00:03:35,933 --> 00:03:39,066
this multiblock has a bunch of options for configuration

97
00:03:39,466 --> 00:03:40,800
to figure out which one you need

98
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,333
you need to know which recipe you're using

99
00:03:42,900 --> 00:03:44,033
to start with distillation

100
00:03:44,033 --> 00:03:47,000
you can distill oil at MV which gives four outputs

101
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:48,333
as the tooltip suggests

102
00:03:48,333 --> 00:03:50,233
you can only have one fluid output per layer

103
00:03:50,233 --> 00:03:52,266
and an item output needs to be in the bottom layer

104
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:54,133
so the tower needs to be five blocks tall

105
00:03:54,466 --> 00:03:55,433
easy enough right

106
00:03:55,900 --> 00:03:56,933
just like the single block

107
00:03:56,933 --> 00:03:58,666
the outputs are contaminated with sulfur

108
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:01,100
and you'll have to mix them with hydrogen to get the clean output

109
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:04,466
if you use a multi block chemical reactor with five input hatches

110
00:04:04,466 --> 00:04:06,500
one for each oil product and one for hydrogen

111
00:04:06,500 --> 00:04:07,700
and two output hatches

112
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:10,600
you can easily desulfurize everything in just one machine

113
00:04:10,900 --> 00:04:12,833
you'll probably need a dedicated hydrogen production

114
00:04:12,833 --> 00:04:16,033
and be sure to save the hydrogen sulfide to turn into sulfuric acid later

115
00:04:16,266 --> 00:04:19,433
you're gonna need every drop of the stuff you can get coming up very soon

116
00:04:19,733 --> 00:04:21,200
once you got the clean outputs

117
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:22,700
it's time to decide what to do with them

118
00:04:22,900 --> 00:04:24,666
here's what I suggest as a starting point

119
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,933
mix the light fuel and heavy fuel to get diesel

120
00:04:27,066 --> 00:04:28,933
you either just got a supplementary fuel source

121
00:04:28,933 --> 00:04:30,533
or you upgraded your existing one

122
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:33,600
send the naphtha into a multi block oil cracker

123
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,700
lightly steam crack it

124
00:04:34,700 --> 00:04:37,400
and then send that into a max size distillation tower

125
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:40,333
the 12 tall behemoth with 11 fluid outputs

126
00:04:40,433 --> 00:04:42,100
and super tanks for everything

127
00:04:42,433 --> 00:04:43,866
every last chemical is useful

128
00:04:43,866 --> 00:04:45,866
and some will be critical shortly

129
00:04:46,466 --> 00:04:47,733
as for the refinery gas

130
00:04:47,733 --> 00:04:50,333
you can steam crack that as well and distill it in a 6 tall tower

131
00:04:50,433 --> 00:04:51,200
but for the moment

132
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,733
if you just want to use a single block distillery

133
00:04:52,733 --> 00:04:55,466
and crank out ethylene to make your polyethylene setup a bit better

134
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:56,633
I wouldn't be mad at you

135
00:04:57,100 --> 00:04:58,866
you'll also get ethylene from the naphtha to set up

136
00:04:58,866 --> 00:05:00,033
so you should be all set

137
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:01,933
if you go with all single blocks

138
00:05:01,933 --> 00:05:03,933
other than the crackers and distillation towers

139
00:05:04,033 --> 00:05:06,266
it'll end up looking something like this once you finish the whole line

140
00:05:06,266 --> 00:05:08,266
by turning the fuel into cetane boosted diesel

141
00:05:08,733 --> 00:05:10,533
huge mess right

142
00:05:11,700 --> 00:05:13,300
so let's circle back to the LCR

143
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:15,066
you're going to be making a lot of these

144
00:05:15,066 --> 00:05:17,033
so no time like the present start using them

145
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:19,200
you'll need the HV tier plastic

146
00:05:19,266 --> 00:05:20,900
polytetrafluoroethylene

147
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:23,833
this is a minor little resource check in the quest book

148
00:05:23,833 --> 00:05:26,266
you'll need decent supplies of fluorine and chlorine

149
00:05:26,333 --> 00:05:29,200
and neither of those are as straightforward to get as the standard gases

150
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:32,100
if you haven't gotten into bees or IC2 crops

151
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:35,866
your best bet is to electrolyze cryolite for fluorine and salt for chlorine

152
00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:37,533
the good news is

153
00:05:37,533 --> 00:05:39,900
you really only need this stuff for LCR's for now

154
00:05:41,066 --> 00:05:43,000
the main reason you want to get into these right away

155
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:45,266
is you can send multiple fluids into them to react

156
00:05:45,433 --> 00:05:47,800
that's right no more cell management

157
00:05:47,933 --> 00:05:49,300
at least for chemical reactors

158
00:05:49,300 --> 00:05:50,866
the gods rejoice

159
00:05:51,066 --> 00:05:53,433
these things can fit tons of input and output hatches

160
00:05:53,433 --> 00:05:54,800
and the outputs can be filtered

161
00:05:55,133 --> 00:05:56,666
just remember to mind the recipes tier

162
00:05:56,666 --> 00:05:58,633
and be smart about how much power you supply

163
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,666
next up, you can start cooking some new boules

164
00:06:01,933 --> 00:06:02,866
to get the phosphorus

165
00:06:02,866 --> 00:06:04,833
you can break down tricalcium phosphate

166
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:07,333
grabbable at apatite vein in the overworld

167
00:06:07,933 --> 00:06:09,733
you'll also need nitrogen in the EBF

168
00:06:09,733 --> 00:06:13,033
which you can get from cell cycling compressed air cells into a centrifuge

169
00:06:13,833 --> 00:06:14,666
once again

170
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:15,833
this is a long smelt

171
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:17,633
good thing you just upgraded your fuel

172
00:06:17,933 --> 00:06:19,266
these aren't a hard requirement

173
00:06:19,266 --> 00:06:20,600
other than to complete the quest

174
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:22,100
but like with the other circuit components

175
00:06:22,100 --> 00:06:24,500
your resources go further the better the input is

176
00:06:25,466 --> 00:06:26,400
while the boules cook

177
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:28,266
it's time to start preparing for the clean room

178
00:06:28,700 --> 00:06:30,800
the quest book does a good job explaining how it works

179
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:32,066
so to summarize briefly

180
00:06:32,466 --> 00:06:34,433
build a 5 by 5 by 5 box

181
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:36,133
put the controller in the top middle

182
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:38,200
surround it with filter machine casings

183
00:06:38,266 --> 00:06:40,200
and make the rest out of plascrete blocks

184
00:06:41,233 --> 00:06:43,000
toss down an LV Energy hatch

185
00:06:43,266 --> 00:06:44,333
a maintenance hatch

186
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:45,200
and a way in

187
00:06:45,933 --> 00:06:48,733
and the last thing you absolutely need is the cable diode

188
00:06:48,900 --> 00:06:51,466
and the 4 amp MV diode will work just fine to begin

189
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:53,300
stick the diode in a wall

190
00:06:53,300 --> 00:06:54,833
and run the right amount of power in

191
00:06:57,066 --> 00:06:58,233
as the quest book suggests

192
00:06:58,233 --> 00:07:00,233
you need to give the cleanroom 40 EU per tick

193
00:07:00,266 --> 00:07:02,466
so two LV generators will do the job

194
00:07:03,133 --> 00:07:04,800
you probably remember from dealing with the EBF

195
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:07,100
that an energy hatch can take 2 amps of power

196
00:07:07,233 --> 00:07:09,000
so send power from both right on in

197
00:07:09,333 --> 00:07:11,300
and don't forget to send the power into the diode too

198
00:07:13,066 --> 00:07:14,000
do some maintenance

199
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,666
then pop on in and turn the cleaner on

200
00:07:16,133 --> 00:07:16,833
if all is well

201
00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:18,000
you'll see it starts working

202
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:21,333
and very slowly increases the efficiency by one percent at a time

203
00:07:21,833 --> 00:07:23,500
anything less than 100% efficiency

204
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:24,733
and you might void an item

205
00:07:24,866 --> 00:07:26,666
and if it happens to be a mainframe circuit

206
00:07:26,666 --> 00:07:28,000
you're gonna have a bad time

207
00:07:28,733 --> 00:07:31,000
opening the door to the clean room lowers the efficiency

208
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:32,933
so replace it with an elevator or a travel anchor

209
00:07:32,933 --> 00:07:34,266
and act like you never made it

210
00:07:35,066 --> 00:07:36,300
run some cable from the diode

211
00:07:36,300 --> 00:07:39,333
and plop down the cutting machine, laser engraver and the circuit assembler

212
00:07:40,266 --> 00:07:42,533
you'll need HV power in the clean room very soon

213
00:07:42,533 --> 00:07:43,433
but for the moment

214
00:07:43,533 --> 00:07:44,333
you're gaming

215
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:47,733
if you figured out chlorine enough to get the polytetra

216
00:07:47,733 --> 00:07:50,733
hopefully you have some spare for a massive batch of iron (III) chloride

217
00:07:51,066 --> 00:07:53,166
you were able to put off the circuit boards last episode

218
00:07:53,166 --> 00:07:54,300
but not anymore

219
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,133
aside from just the chlorine

220
00:07:56,133 --> 00:08:01,733
you're about to use the most insane quantity of copper that you have ever seen required by modded Minecraft

221
00:08:01,733 --> 00:08:02,666
at least so far

222
00:08:03,233 --> 00:08:05,466
be sure to use the best recipes you can afford

223
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:07,833
and if you think you have enough circuit supplies

224
00:08:07,833 --> 00:08:08,666
you don't

225
00:08:09,233 --> 00:08:11,800
it might take an entire day to accumulate enough stuff here

226
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:13,733
start with eight stacks of boards

227
00:08:13,733 --> 00:08:15,433
but be ready for eight more behind that

228
00:08:16,266 --> 00:08:18,233
the circuit quantities are about to explode

229
00:08:18,700 --> 00:08:21,133
to make the single IV mainframe you need for the quest

230
00:08:21,133 --> 00:08:23,200
you'll need 14 plastic boards

231
00:08:23,466 --> 00:08:24,900
it escalates quickly from here

232
00:08:27,666 --> 00:08:28,700
on the bright side

233
00:08:28,700 --> 00:08:32,000
you can make ULV, LV and MV circuits in a single step now

234
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,466
and for as cheap as they're gonna get

235
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:35,233
stock up on LV circuits

236
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:36,133
you'll need them

237
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,866
and once you've worked your way up to the EV circuit

238
00:08:38,866 --> 00:08:43,533
which by the way use a fluid extractor-fluid solidifier combination for the blue alloy bolts

239
00:08:43,533 --> 00:08:44,533
you'll thank yourself

240
00:08:45,066 --> 00:08:46,333
you can make the vacuum freezer

241
00:08:46,333 --> 00:08:48,100
which you should do as a priority

242
00:08:48,700 --> 00:08:50,133
no more silly coolant cooling

243
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:51,733
and no better time either

244
00:08:51,733 --> 00:08:54,833
because you've just realized how important those cheaper circuit components are

245
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:59,666
and you want to cook copious volumes of tantalum you've just extracted from the nether with your shiny new miners

246
00:09:01,966 --> 00:09:05,600
so add an HV diode, an HV generator and the HV circuit assembler

247
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:07,433
and make your first IV circuits

248
00:09:07,666 --> 00:09:09,433
my God they're pricey

249
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:12,700
and go ahead and make the NASA workbench too

250
00:09:12,833 --> 00:09:14,133
it'll make you feel good to have it

251
00:09:14,233 --> 00:09:15,200
however briefly

252
00:09:16,033 --> 00:09:18,033
you can grab the implosion compressor now as well

253
00:09:18,066 --> 00:09:19,700
at this point an easy craft

254
00:09:19,933 --> 00:09:22,533
the problem is you need explosives

255
00:09:23,433 --> 00:09:26,833
I'm going to take this as another opportunity to encourage getting into bees

256
00:09:26,833 --> 00:09:31,100
because staying in supply of iTNT without them is going to be a little bit more complicated

257
00:09:31,733 --> 00:09:33,733
another shameless plug of Aditya's bees guide

258
00:09:33,866 --> 00:09:35,500
watch them, use them

259
00:09:35,633 --> 00:09:36,933
hold them in highest esteem

260
00:09:37,866 --> 00:09:39,533
in case that doesn't interest you at all

261
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:40,800
here's your alternatives

262
00:09:41,266 --> 00:09:43,700
more setups for hydrogen oxygen and nitrogen

263
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:45,333
being used to make ammonia

264
00:09:45,333 --> 00:09:46,466
nitrogen oxide

265
00:09:46,466 --> 00:09:47,800
nitrogen dioxide

266
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:49,500
and then nitric acid

267
00:09:50,300 --> 00:09:52,600
it's still a bit early to centralize fluids easily

268
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:55,133
but you'll need these chemicals again for the cetane-boosted diesel

269
00:09:55,133 --> 00:09:56,200
so keep that in mind

270
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:58,900
you can probably share at least this setup if you're smart

271
00:09:59,866 --> 00:10:03,200
if you're mixing sulfuric acid from the hydrogen sulfide you're getting from the oil line

272
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:05,266
route some over here and combine it with a nitric acid

273
00:10:05,633 --> 00:10:08,300
otherwise divert some oxygen from your local setup

274
00:10:08,433 --> 00:10:12,000
and mix some fresh on site to combine with a nitric acid for a nitration mixture

275
00:10:12,266 --> 00:10:14,600
and use the LCR recipe, it's easier

276
00:10:15,133 --> 00:10:17,033
you got the toluene from distilling naphtha

277
00:10:17,266 --> 00:10:20,200
so send it through a ball mold in the fluid solidifier for gelled toluene

278
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:21,800
if you're set up for it

279
00:10:21,800 --> 00:10:24,700
you get better returns on the toluene using sugar and polyethylene

280
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:27,066
but when's the last time you checked on your farms

281
00:10:28,233 --> 00:10:30,533
do bees really seem that bad to do now

282
00:10:30,866 --> 00:10:32,433
it's not getting any better from here

283
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:33,600
trust me

284
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:35,966
after you have a couple dozen stacks of iTNT or so

285
00:10:35,966 --> 00:10:37,700
you can make compressed plates

286
00:10:38,300 --> 00:10:41,066
you're going to use an insane amount of resources here

287
00:10:41,066 --> 00:10:42,433
if you follow the order of the guide

288
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:46,300
this represents days and days of effort and smelting and crafting

289
00:10:46,633 --> 00:10:47,933
the videos have been snappy

290
00:10:47,933 --> 00:10:50,266
but don't mistake that for progress being fast

291
00:10:52,066 --> 00:10:55,300
as usual the quest book does an excellent job of laying out the steps

292
00:10:55,300 --> 00:10:56,666
you need most of the stuff here

293
00:10:56,933 --> 00:10:59,333
slowly but surely make your way towards the rocket

294
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:00,400
the tier 1 lander

295
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:01,466
the oxygen gear

296
00:11:01,466 --> 00:11:02,600
and the launch equipment

297
00:11:03,700 --> 00:11:04,666
and when you have it all

298
00:11:04,666 --> 00:11:06,200
you'll need to gas up the beast

299
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:07,733
you have two choices

300
00:11:07,866 --> 00:11:10,466
cetane-boosted diesel or RP1 rocket fuel

301
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:14,200
and cetane is going to be pretty easy if you follow it along pretty closely

302
00:11:14,833 --> 00:11:17,900
you've got nitric acid and sulfuric acid standing by for making TNT

303
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:19,333
and extra ethylene from distilling naphtha

304
00:11:19,333 --> 00:11:21,333
you can mix with oxygen for acetic acid

305
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:23,333
the last chemical you need to get ethenone

306
00:11:23,466 --> 00:11:26,733
and ultimately tetranitromethane once you react it with the nitric acid

307
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,466
mix that with a bit of fuel

308
00:11:28,466 --> 00:11:29,866
and you're ready for space flight

309
00:11:30,333 --> 00:11:32,033
if you can automate this whole process

310
00:11:32,033 --> 00:11:34,633
this is a pretty big upgrade from regular fuel for your base too

311
00:11:36,100 --> 00:11:37,466
snag up that space gear

312
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:39,066
and it's time for final checks

313
00:11:39,133 --> 00:11:40,466
and be sure you make them

314
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:42,633
go ahead and fill your oxygen

315
00:11:42,933 --> 00:11:45,200
you'll notice that the galacticraft blocks are sided

316
00:11:45,233 --> 00:11:47,000
so make sure the energy is actually going in

317
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:49,400
and the oxygen is actually coming out on the collector

318
00:11:49,433 --> 00:11:51,233
and that both are going in on the compressor

319
00:11:51,700 --> 00:11:52,866
goofy little blocks

320
00:11:53,133 --> 00:11:54,333
and don't forget to bring them with you

321
00:11:55,666 --> 00:11:57,033
then it's confirming:

322
00:11:57,033 --> 00:12:06,433
oxygen, tanks, miners, compressed chests, generators, fuel, leaves, a fuel loader, glowstone torches, EnderIO capacitor and energy conduits

323
00:12:07,133 --> 00:12:08,266
check check check

324
00:12:09,033 --> 00:12:10,533
you can collect oxygen on the moon too

325
00:12:10,533 --> 00:12:12,233
that's why you're bringing the stack of leaves

326
00:12:12,233 --> 00:12:13,300
just cut out a cave

327
00:12:13,300 --> 00:12:14,166
line them with leaves

328
00:12:14,166 --> 00:12:15,333
and plop the collector down

329
00:12:16,100 --> 00:12:17,833
the more leaves close by the better

330
00:12:18,433 --> 00:12:19,233
and with that

331
00:12:19,466 --> 00:12:20,600
you're ready to launch

332
00:12:20,866 --> 00:12:21,833
don't forget anything

333
00:12:58,833 --> 00:12:59,833
mission control

334
00:12:59,833 --> 00:13:00,866
this is flight commander

335
00:13:01,066 --> 00:13:02,066
we have impact

336
00:13:03,433 --> 00:13:04,533
no time to waste

337
00:13:04,833 --> 00:13:07,000
slay monsters and light the night if you need to

338
00:13:07,066 --> 00:13:08,833
otherwise get right to work prospecting

339
00:13:08,833 --> 00:13:10,600
and looking around for the dungeon entrance

340
00:13:10,666 --> 00:13:12,100
basically just a big hole in the ground

341
00:13:12,100 --> 00:13:13,700
and you can see bricks at the bottom of it

342
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:19,300
you're looking for neodymium, bauxite, ilmenite, chromite and aluminum

343
00:13:19,833 --> 00:13:22,033
tons of goodies here to supply life on earth

344
00:13:22,466 --> 00:13:25,033
get your miners out. get them set, and get them chunk loaded

345
00:13:25,033 --> 00:13:26,133
then go boss hunting

346
00:13:27,700 --> 00:13:28,733
even if you can't fly

347
00:13:28,733 --> 00:13:31,466
you can really just zip right through the dungeon straight to the boss arena

348
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:34,700
and kill the boss very very easily

349
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:50,433
grab the key, check the chest

350
00:13:50,433 --> 00:13:52,866
and cross your fingers for a tier 2 rocket template

351
00:14:02,700 --> 00:14:03,500
eh

352
00:14:03,733 --> 00:14:04,666
if you don't get one

353
00:14:04,666 --> 00:14:07,100
find more dungeons and kill more bosses until you do

354
00:14:07,100 --> 00:14:08,200
it won't take long

355
00:14:10,433 --> 00:14:12,433
once you're content with your haul, head on home

356
00:14:12,733 --> 00:14:15,200
don't feel bad about making a home location on the moon either

357
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:17,300
no one is judging you because no one knows you did it

358
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:21,800
and all that's left now

359
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:24,133
is processing the aluminate and bauxite into rutile

360
00:14:25,933 --> 00:14:28,666
full on maxing out the production is going to be worth it here

361
00:14:28,666 --> 00:14:30,733
so macerate the bauxite ore down to crush form

362
00:14:30,733 --> 00:14:32,966
then send it through a chemical bath with sodium persulfate

363
00:14:33,533 --> 00:14:36,900
you can expand on this by processing the purified bauxite into bauxite slurry

364
00:14:36,900 --> 00:14:38,866
and investing in the full bauxite line

365
00:14:39,133 --> 00:14:41,266
we ain't going to cover it now, but look it up

366
00:14:41,333 --> 00:14:44,133
insane returns, insane

367
00:14:44,733 --> 00:14:46,600
you can do some similar things with the ilmenite too

368
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:48,133
except using sulfuric acid for insane returns on rutile

369
00:14:48,133 --> 00:14:49,833
（向上合并）

370
00:14:49,833 --> 00:14:52,100
and a closed loop for getting the sulfuric acid back

371
00:14:52,266 --> 00:14:53,200
but not until EV

372
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:54,466
if you're desperate

373
00:14:54,466 --> 00:14:56,066
you can run ilmenite through the full

374
00:14:56,066 --> 00:14:58,300
macerator-washer-macerator-centrifuge line

375
00:14:58,300 --> 00:14:59,433
for some bonus rutile

376
00:14:59,733 --> 00:15:02,000
but you're probably better off just getting more bauxite

377
00:15:03,300 --> 00:15:04,533
once you're all set on rutile

378
00:15:04,533 --> 00:15:06,333
you can start converting it into titanium

379
00:15:07,133 --> 00:15:08,333
the quest book explains it

380
00:15:08,333 --> 00:15:08,866
but in short

381
00:15:08,866 --> 00:15:10,833
the whole processing line is a giant closed loop

382
00:15:10,833 --> 00:15:12,333
where the only input is rutile

383
00:15:12,833 --> 00:15:13,533
to kick start it

384
00:15:13,533 --> 00:15:16,266
you need chlorine and carbon to go with the rutile at an LCR

385
00:15:16,633 --> 00:15:18,666
electrolyze the resulting carbon monoxide

386
00:15:18,666 --> 00:15:21,333
send the titanium chloride to the EBF with magnesium

387
00:15:21,633 --> 00:15:23,300
cool the resulting hot titanium

388
00:15:23,300 --> 00:15:27,466
and send the magnesium chloride to a chemical reactor to combine with sodium for the magnesium back

389
00:15:27,466 --> 00:15:31,633
and some salt which you can electrolyze for your original chlorine and the sodium you just used

390
00:15:32,700 --> 00:15:34,400
all it takes is a little logistics

391
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:36,400
and it can run as long as you stay in rutile

392
00:15:39,300 --> 00:15:42,533
and you're gonna want to run it for a long long time

393
00:15:43,066 --> 00:15:43,866
you've done it

394
00:15:43,900 --> 00:15:45,100
you're out of the early game

395
00:15:45,300 --> 00:15:47,533
you're officially no longer a beginner

396
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:49,466
just in time for new beginnings

397
00:15:49,666 --> 00:15:51,133
this is GTNH after all

398
00:15:51,333 --> 00:15:52,933
the learning is never done

399
00:15:53,666 --> 00:15:55,333
there's a lot more to do in HV too

400
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:56,800
but you know how to look around now

401
00:15:57,266 --> 00:15:59,466
Applied Energistics is on the horizon

402
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:01,633
if you can get enough titanium that is

403
00:16:02,033 --> 00:16:05,700
hopefully this guide sets you up with enough information to take a real crack at the pack

404
00:16:05,933 --> 00:16:06,933
you won't regret it

405
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:08,333
see you in the game

406
00:16:08,866 --> 00:16:11,233
and hey stay positive out there

407
00:00:02,033 --> 00:00:02,933
就是现在

408
00:00:03,333 --> 00:00:05,866
你的发电

409
00:00:06,200 --> 00:00:08,066
你的化工仓储都快爆仓了

410
00:00:08,833 --> 00:00:11,200
你的高炉已经运行了好几天了

411
00:00:11,866 --> 00:00:13,666
你手里不锈钢多到离谱

412
00:00:14,066 --> 00:00:16,733
但现在你得迈向其他星球

413
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:19,866
太空的真空对没做好准备的人是致命的

414
00:00:20,833 --> 00:00:21,866
但这就是你为什么点开这个视频

415
00:00:22,066 --> 00:00:23,433
现在到了冲刺阶段

416
00:00:23,666 --> 00:00:25,333
你已经站在中期的门槛上

417
00:00:25,733 --> 00:00:27,500
准备告别新手阶段

418
00:00:27,833 --> 00:00:30,000
所以这次我们将奔赴太空

419
00:00:30,233 --> 00:00:31,833
这是第八集

420
00:00:32,133 --> 00:00:32,933
HV

421
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:35,633
向着渺渺星辰进发

422
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:50,300
MV任务基本是一条直线推进

423
00:00:50,533 --> 00:00:52,200
一个漂亮的小独立章节

424
00:00:52,633 --> 00:00:54,133
HV则相反

425
00:00:54,466 --> 00:00:56,833
你会在任务书里跳来跳去

426
00:00:57,500 --> 00:00:59,100
这些基本套路你应该已经熟了

427
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:01,000
所以还是先从“你会讨厌这个的”任务开始

428
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:02,200
只是提醒一下

429
00:01:02,233 --> 00:01:04,500
每个电压阶段都会有一堆新内容

430
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:06,433
但也总有一些重复的老套路

431
00:01:08,200 --> 00:01:09,400
制造机器部件

432
00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:11,100
升级机器

433
00:01:11,333 --> 00:01:12,700
做能源仓

434
00:01:12,866 --> 00:01:13,800
制作线圈

435
00:01:14,133 --> 00:01:15,100
制造塑料

436
00:01:15,633 --> 00:01:17,100
并改进电路板

437
00:01:17,433 --> 00:01:18,900
有时顺序会发生变化

438
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:21,066
有些事你可以拖很久再做

439
00:01:21,266 --> 00:01:23,066
但最后你都得补课

440
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:25,600
假设你已经烧好了需要的不锈钢

441
00:01:25,600 --> 00:01:27,200
也别忘了继续挖基础矿物

442
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:28,466
尤其是铜

443
00:01:28,733 --> 00:01:30,633
没有什么可以阻挡你去挖铜

444
00:01:31,133 --> 00:01:32,833
你可以立刻做MV电路组装机

445
00:01:32,833 --> 00:01:34,266
电路板生产速度会直接起飞

446
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:37,200
不过有超净间之前你还做不了新电路板

447
00:01:37,466 --> 00:01:38,300
我们后面会讲到这一点

448
00:01:38,466 --> 00:01:40,000
你现在可以利用它的处理速度的提升

449
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,633
并获得一些重要的升级

450
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:45,133
HV矿机非常值得拥有

451
00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:48,033
也是你迈向多方块采矿机前的最后一站

452
00:01:48,133 --> 00:01:49,100
直接做3到4台

453
00:01:49,100 --> 00:01:51,666
让它们全天不停机

454
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:53,333
压缩箱子也顺手做上

455
00:01:53,666 --> 00:01:54,466
它们很贵

456
00:01:54,466 --> 00:01:56,066
但是优点是拆掉会保留内容物

457
00:01:56,066 --> 00:01:58,933
对采矿流程来说是极大的提升

458
00:01:59,466 --> 00:02:01,666
HV机器还增加了一个输出槽

459
00:02:01,666 --> 00:02:05,300
这样你能在矿处的各阶段获得副产物

460
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:07,466
不是每种副产物都值得留下

461
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:08,933
有些只会把产线堵死

462
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:13,033
所以这阶段若没用上一些魔法手段，过滤和自动化会有点难办

463
00:02:13,066 --> 00:02:16,033
配几台研磨机、洗矿机和离心机

464
00:02:16,033 --> 00:02:17,933
你的资源就能一直很充足

465
00:02:18,233 --> 00:02:20,500
尤其是铜处理，能产出不少额外的金

466
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:22,500
但是很多东西都值得一试

467
00:02:22,700 --> 00:02:24,300
镍矿先过研磨

468
00:02:24,300 --> 00:02:26,066
再过汞化学浸洗

469
00:02:26,066 --> 00:02:28,200
能在前期顺带得到可观的铂产出

470
00:02:28,900 --> 00:02:30,866
你应该把车间里的机器都升级一遍

471
00:02:30,866 --> 00:02:33,000
但直到你的化工和硅等被动产线速度跟不上之前

472
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:34,933
（向上合并）

473
00:02:34,933 --> 00:02:36,300
别急着升级

474
00:02:36,333 --> 00:02:39,033
不然只会更早跳电

475
00:02:39,266 --> 00:02:39,733
在这个阶段

476
00:02:39,733 --> 00:02:43,733
这个阶段最吃电的是EBF和你新搭的矿处

477
00:02:44,133 --> 00:02:46,000
用你所有的燃料来维持它们的运转

478
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,900
有余电再供给车间

479
00:02:48,233 --> 00:02:50,866
如果没有，现在你可以利用你的之前蒸汽基础设施

480
00:02:50,866 --> 00:02:53,733
给手搓用的机器慢慢充电也行

481
00:02:54,300 --> 00:02:57,333
等电池充电再用单方块很烦

482
00:02:57,333 --> 00:03:01,200
但EBF吞材料后返工更痛苦

483
00:03:01,633 --> 00:03:03,500
如果你已经等得受不了了

484
00:03:03,500 --> 00:03:05,200
就该扩建发电了

485
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:06,633
如果你的发电撑得住

486
00:03:06,633 --> 00:03:07,933
就直接去做超净间

487
00:03:08,033 --> 00:03:09,866
不管怎么样，以下的建议你都应该听听

488
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,266
如果你是走石油发电路线

489
00:03:12,266 --> 00:03:13,700
坦白说，即使没有

490
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:15,400
你也该考虑上油气流体钻机

491
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,700
再配长距离管道

492
00:03:17,233 --> 00:03:18,500
拿探矿器在基岩上勘探

493
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:20,233
找一个普通原油的虚拟油气田

494
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:22,133
地下油田的储量非常大

495
00:03:22,133 --> 00:03:24,400
能保证你在这里抽很长一段时间

496
00:03:24,866 --> 00:03:26,300
把多方块油气流体钻机搭起来

497
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:28,033
接好长距离管道输入

498
00:03:28,033 --> 00:03:28,866
加载区块

499
00:03:28,900 --> 00:03:31,100
一路铺管道回到基地

500
00:03:32,266 --> 00:03:33,500
当你回来的时候

501
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:35,500
把原油送进你新建的蒸馏塔

502
00:03:35,933 --> 00:03:39,066
这个多方块有不少配置方案

503
00:03:39,466 --> 00:03:40,800
要弄清楚你改用哪一个

504
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,333
先看你跑的是哪条配方

505
00:03:42,900 --> 00:03:44,033
从蒸馏开始

506
00:03:44,033 --> 00:03:47,000
MV阶段蒸馏原油会给4种输出

507
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:48,333
正如 tooltip 写的那样

508
00:03:48,333 --> 00:03:50,233
每一层最多放一个流体输出仓

509
00:03:50,233 --> 00:03:52,266
物品输出必须放底层

510
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:54,133
所以塔至少要5层高

511
00:03:54,466 --> 00:03:55,433
很容易对吧

512
00:03:55,900 --> 00:03:56,933
就像单方块蒸馏一样

513
00:03:56,933 --> 00:03:58,666
这些输出的馏分都含硫

514
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:01,100
要和氢反应脱硫后才是洁净产物

515
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:04,466
如果你使用有五个输入仓的大化反

516
00:04:04,466 --> 00:04:06,500
每种石油产物一个输入仓，再加一个氢输入仓

517
00:04:06,500 --> 00:04:07,700
再配两个输出仓

518
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:10,600
一台机器就能把整套产物都脱硫

519
00:04:10,900 --> 00:04:12,833
你可能需要专门的制氢设备

520
00:04:12,833 --> 00:04:16,033
记得把硫化氢存起来，后面做硫酸要用

521
00:04:16,266 --> 00:04:19,433
你很快就会需要每一滴你能拿到的东西

522
00:04:19,733 --> 00:04:21,200
一旦你得到干净的输出

523
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:22,700
是时候决定怎么处理它们了

524
00:04:22,900 --> 00:04:24,666
我建议起步这样配

525
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,933
轻燃油和重燃油混合成柴油

526
00:04:27,066 --> 00:04:28,933
这样你要么多了一个补充燃料源

527
00:04:28,933 --> 00:04:30,533
要么直接提升了你的现有燃料产线

528
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:33,600
石脑油送进多方块石油裂化机

529
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,700
轻度蒸汽裂化

530
00:04:34,700 --> 00:04:37,400
再送进满配蒸馏塔

531
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:40,333
也就是12层高、11个流体输出的蒸馏塔

532
00:04:40,433 --> 00:04:42,100
每一个输出仓都配超级缸

533
00:04:42,433 --> 00:04:43,866
每一种化学品都用得上

534
00:04:43,866 --> 00:04:45,866
有些产物很快就会发挥关键作用

535
00:04:46,466 --> 00:04:47,733
至于炼油气

536
00:04:47,733 --> 00:04:50,333
它也能蒸汽裂化后，送进6层高的蒸馏塔蒸馏

537
00:04:50,433 --> 00:04:51,200
但目前

538
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,733
如果你暂时只想用单方块蒸馏机

539
00:04:52,733 --> 00:04:55,466
先多产点乙烯去喂聚乙烯产线

540
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:56,633
我完全能理解

541
00:04:57,100 --> 00:04:58,866
你还可以从石脑油中提取乙烯

542
00:04:58,866 --> 00:05:00,033
你应该都准备好了

543
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:01,933
如果你选择所有机器都用单方块

544
00:05:01,933 --> 00:05:03,933
除了石油裂化机和蒸馏塔

545
00:05:04,033 --> 00:05:06,266
如果你搭好了整条产线，它大概看起来这样

546
00:05:06,266 --> 00:05:08,266
把柴油变成高十六烷值柴油

547
00:05:08,733 --> 00:05:10,533
是不是一团麻花？

548
00:05:11,700 --> 00:05:13,300
所以让我们回到大化反

549
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:15,066
你要做很多这样的东西

550
00:05:15,066 --> 00:05:17,033
所以现在就开始用最合适

551
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:19,200
你需要HV等级的塑料

552
00:05:19,266 --> 00:05:20,900
聚四氟乙烯

553
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:23,833
这在任务书里算个小资源门槛

554
00:05:23,833 --> 00:05:26,266
你需要足够的氟和氯

555
00:05:26,333 --> 00:05:29,200
这两种气体都不像标准气体那样容易获得

556
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:32,100
如果你没有碰蜜蜂或IC2作物

557
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:35,866
最好的办法是电解冰晶石生成氟，电解盐生成氯

558
00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:37,533
好消息是

559
00:05:37,533 --> 00:05:39,900
至少在当前阶段，这东西主要就是拿来做大化反

560
00:05:41,066 --> 00:05:43,000
你要尽快做出它的核心原因是

561
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:45,266
它能直接对多种流体输入进行化学反应

562
00:05:45,433 --> 00:05:47,800
没错，告别单元管理

563
00:05:47,933 --> 00:05:49,300
至少对化学反应釜来说

564
00:05:49,300 --> 00:05:50,866
隔壁小孩儿都乐哭了

565
00:05:51,066 --> 00:05:53,433
这东西可以放一大堆输入和输出仓

566
00:05:53,433 --> 00:05:54,800
并且可以过滤输出

567
00:05:55,133 --> 00:05:56,666
只是记得注意配方的电压等级

568
00:05:56,666 --> 00:05:58,633
合理控制供电多少

569
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,666
接下来，可以开始烧新的单晶硅

570
00:06:01,933 --> 00:06:02,866
要得到磷

571
00:06:02,866 --> 00:06:04,833
可以处理磷酸三钙

572
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:07,333
主世界的磷灰石矿脉就能挖到

573
00:06:07,933 --> 00:06:09,733
电高炉中还需要氮气

574
00:06:09,733 --> 00:06:13,033
可以把压缩空气单元循环送离心机来产氮

575
00:06:13,833 --> 00:06:14,666
再一次

576
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:15,833
这又是一轮长时间烧炼

577
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:17,633
幸好你刚升级了燃料

578
00:06:17,933 --> 00:06:19,266
这些不是硬性要求

579
00:06:19,266 --> 00:06:20,600
除了完成任务

580
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:22,100
但就像其他的电路板组件一样

581
00:06:22,100 --> 00:06:24,500
你的原料越好，产品就越高级

582
00:06:25,466 --> 00:06:26,400
在单晶硅慢慢烧的同时

583
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:28,266
就该开始准备超净间了

584
00:06:28,700 --> 00:06:30,800
任务书解释得很明白

585
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:32,066
简单总结一下

586
00:06:32,466 --> 00:06:34,433
建一个5x5x5的盒子

587
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:36,133
将控制器放在顶部中间

588
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:38,200
用过滤机械方块包围它

589
00:06:38,266 --> 00:06:40,200
其余部分用塑料混凝土方块

590
00:06:41,233 --> 00:06:43,000
放一个LV能源仓

591
00:06:43,266 --> 00:06:44,333
维护仓

592
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:45,200
再留一个入口

593
00:06:45,933 --> 00:06:48,733
最后还必须有线缆二极管

594
00:06:48,900 --> 00:06:51,466
4A MV二极管就够了

595
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:53,300
把二极管塞入墙里

596
00:06:53,300 --> 00:06:54,833
接入合适的电力

597
00:06:57,066 --> 00:06:58,233
正如任务书写的那样

598
00:06:58,233 --> 00:07:00,233
超净间需要持续消耗40 EU/t

599
00:07:00,266 --> 00:07:02,466
所以两台LV发电机就能带起来

600
00:07:03,133 --> 00:07:04,800
你应该还记得EBF那套供电规则

601
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:07,100
能源仓能吃2A输入

602
00:07:07,233 --> 00:07:09,000
所以两路电都直接喂进去

603
00:07:09,333 --> 00:07:11,300
别忘了把电也送到二极管里

604
00:07:13,066 --> 00:07:14,000
先把维护做了

605
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,666
然后进去把超净间开起来

606
00:07:16,133 --> 00:07:16,833
如果一切顺利

607
00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:18,000
你会看到它开始工作了

608
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:21,333
效率会很慢地每次涨1%

609
00:07:21,833 --> 00:07:23,500
只要低于100%效率

610
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:24,733
就有概率配方失败

611
00:07:24,866 --> 00:07:26,666
如果它碰巧是一个主机电路板

612
00:07:26,666 --> 00:07:28,000
你的天空会是灰蓝色的

613
00:07:28,733 --> 00:07:31,000
打开超净间的门会降低效率

614
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:32,933
所以你可以转用电梯或旅行锚

615
00:07:32,933 --> 00:07:34,266
当它从来没装过门就行

616
00:07:35,066 --> 00:07:36,300
从二极管接出一些电缆

617
00:07:36,300 --> 00:07:39,333
把切割机、激光刻蚀机和电路组装机摆进去

618
00:07:40,266 --> 00:07:42,533
超净间很快就要用HV电了

619
00:07:42,533 --> 00:07:43,433
但目前

620
00:07:43,533 --> 00:07:44,333
你已经起飞了

621
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:47,733
如果你的氯足够制造聚四氟乙烯

622
00:07:47,733 --> 00:07:50,733
希望你还有余量做一大批三氯化铁

623
00:07:51,066 --> 00:07:53,166
上集你还能暂时不做电路基板

624
00:07:53,166 --> 00:07:54,300
但这集不行了

625
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,133
除了氯

626
00:07:56,133 --> 00:08:01,733
你马上会见识到MC整合包史上最离谱的铜消耗

627
00:08:01,733 --> 00:08:02,666
至少是目前为止最多的

628
00:08:03,233 --> 00:08:05,466
务必使用你负担得起的最高级配方

629
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:07,833
如果你以为你有足够的电路板库存

630
00:08:07,833 --> 00:08:08,666
不，你没有

631
00:08:09,233 --> 00:08:11,800
你可能要花一整天才能攒出这里展示的东西

632
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:13,733
先做8组电路基板起步

633
00:08:13,733 --> 00:08:15,433
然后准备好再做8组

634
00:08:16,266 --> 00:08:18,233
电路板数量即将爆炸

635
00:08:18,700 --> 00:08:21,133
为了任务里的那一个IV主机

636
00:08:21,133 --> 00:08:23,200
你就得花费14块塑料电路基板

637
00:08:23,466 --> 00:08:24,900
后面只会要得越来越多

638
00:08:27,666 --> 00:08:28,700
往好了看

639
00:08:28,700 --> 00:08:32,000
现在ULV、LV、MV电路板都能一步合成

640
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,466
而且成本已经最低了

641
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:35,233
赶紧囤LV电路板

642
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:36,133
你会需要它们的

643
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,866
当你一路做到EV电路板

644
00:08:38,866 --> 00:08:43,533
顺便一提，使用流体提取器+流体固化器制作蓝色合金螺栓

645
00:08:43,533 --> 00:08:44,533
你会感谢自己的

646
00:08:45,066 --> 00:08:46,333
你就能做真空冷冻机

647
00:08:46,333 --> 00:08:48,100
这个必须优先做

648
00:08:48,700 --> 00:08:50,133
再也不用那套拉完了的冷却液降温

649
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:51,733
现在就是换代最好的时候

650
00:08:51,733 --> 00:08:54,833
因为你已经意识到了便宜的电路元件有多重要

651
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:59,666
你会想大规模烧新矿机从下界挖来的钽

652
00:09:01,966 --> 00:09:05,600
那就加一个HV二极管、HV发电机和HV电路组装机

653
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:07,433
做出你的第一批IV电路板

654
00:09:07,666 --> 00:09:09,433
天哪，太贵了

655
00:09:10,900 --> 00:09:12,700
NASA工作台也顺手做了

656
00:09:12,833 --> 00:09:14,133
拥有它会让你感觉很好

657
00:09:14,233 --> 00:09:15,200
感觉很好，暂时的

658
00:09:16,033 --> 00:09:18,033
你现在也可以做出聚爆压缩机了

659
00:09:18,066 --> 00:09:19,700
这个阶段它已经不算难做

660
00:09:19,933 --> 00:09:22,533
问题是你需要爆炸物

661
00:09:23,433 --> 00:09:26,833
我再借机劝一次：去养蜂

662
00:09:26,833 --> 00:09:31,100
不养蜂的话，持续供应工业TNT会很麻烦

663
00:09:31,733 --> 00:09:33,733
再次无耻安利Aditya的养蜂指南

664
00:09:33,866 --> 00:09:35,500
去看，去用

665
00:09:35,633 --> 00:09:36,933
并致以最高敬意

666
00:09:37,866 --> 00:09:39,533
如果你一点都不感兴趣

667
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:40,800
替代方案是：

668
00:09:41,266 --> 00:09:43,700
做更多的氢气、氧气和氮气产线

669
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:45,333
用于合成氨

670
00:09:45,333 --> 00:09:46,466
一氧化氮

671
00:09:46,466 --> 00:09:47,800
二氧化氮

672
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:49,500
然后是硝酸

673
00:09:50,300 --> 00:09:52,600
这阶段想集中流体还太早

674
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:55,133
但这些化学原料后面做高十六烷值柴油还会再用到

675
00:09:55,133 --> 00:09:56,200
所以记住这一点

676
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:58,900
如果你聪明的话，你至少可以共用这个产线

677
00:09:59,866 --> 00:10:03,200
如果你在用石油产线里的硫化氢来混合出硫酸

678
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:05,266
分一点硫酸到这边，和硝酸混合

679
00:10:05,633 --> 00:10:08,300
或者从附近的产线里借一些氧气

680
00:10:08,433 --> 00:10:12,000
当场生产硫酸，再和硝酸混合出硝酸混酸

681
00:10:12,266 --> 00:10:14,600
这一步用大化反配方更省事

682
00:10:15,133 --> 00:10:17,033
你从蒸馏石脑油中得到甲苯

683
00:10:17,266 --> 00:10:20,200
把甲苯通入球模具的流体固化机做出胶凝甲苯

684
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:21,800
如果你准备好了

685
00:10:21,800 --> 00:10:24,700
如果条件允许，用糖+聚乙烯能让甲苯产率更高

686
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:27,066
但是你上次检查你的农场是什么时候？

687
00:10:28,233 --> 00:10:30,533
你现在还觉得蜜蜂很难搞吗？

688
00:10:30,866 --> 00:10:32,433
后面只会更难搞

689
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:33,600
相信我

690
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:35,966
在你有几十组工业TNT之后

691
00:10:35,966 --> 00:10:37,700
你可以做压缩板了

692
00:10:38,300 --> 00:10:41,066
你需要在此挥霍大量资源

693
00:10:41,066 --> 00:10:42,433
如果你按教程的顺序推进

694
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:46,300
这代表了日复一日的努力、烧制和合成

695
00:10:46,633 --> 00:10:47,933
视频剪得很快

696
00:10:47,933 --> 00:10:50,266
但别误会成线下的进度也很快

697
00:10:52,066 --> 00:10:55,300
任务书的指引一如既往的好

698
00:10:55,300 --> 00:10:56,666
你需要这里的大部分东西

699
00:10:56,933 --> 00:10:59,333
慢慢一步一步做出火箭

700
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:00,400
1阶着陆器

701
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:01,466
供氧装置

702
00:11:01,466 --> 00:11:02,600
发射设备

703
00:11:03,700 --> 00:11:04,666
当你拥有了这一切

704
00:11:04,666 --> 00:11:06,200
你得给这大家伙加满燃料

705
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:07,733
你有两个选择

706
00:11:07,866 --> 00:11:10,466
高十六烷值柴油或RP-1火箭燃料

707
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:14,200
按流程走的话，高十六烷比较轻松

708
00:11:14,833 --> 00:11:17,900
你已经在制造TNT的时候准备了硝酸和硫酸

709
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:19,333
再加上蒸馏石脑油拿到的额外乙烯

710
00:11:19,333 --> 00:11:21,333
你可以和氧气混合制乙酸

711
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:23,333
这是合成乙烯酮所需的最后一种化学品

712
00:11:23,466 --> 00:11:26,733
把乙烯酮和硝酸反应得到四硝基甲烷

713
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,466
把它和一些柴油混合

714
00:11:28,466 --> 00:11:29,866
你就已经准备好上太空了

715
00:11:30,333 --> 00:11:32,033
如果你能自动化整个过程

716
00:11:32,033 --> 00:11:34,633
这对你的基地来说也是一个相当大的升级

717
00:11:36,100 --> 00:11:37,466
拿齐太空装备

718
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:39,066
现在是最后检查的时候了

719
00:11:39,133 --> 00:11:40,466
一定要确认每项都有

720
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:42,633
先把氧气补满

721
00:11:42,933 --> 00:11:45,200
你会发现星系模组的机器区分朝向

722
00:11:45,233 --> 00:11:47,000
务必确认电确实进去了

723
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:49,400
氧气确实从收集器出来

724
00:11:49,433 --> 00:11:51,233
压缩机里面电和氧气都够

725
00:11:51,700 --> 00:11:52,866
难用的机器

726
00:11:53,133 --> 00:11:54,333
别忘了带上它们

727
00:11:55,666 --> 00:11:57,033
然后确认最终清单：

728
00:11:57,033 --> 00:12:06,433
氧气、储罐、矿机、压缩箱子、发电机、燃料、树叶、燃料注入机、萤石火把、EIO电容与能量导管

729
00:12:07,133 --> 00:12:08,266
勾上，勾上，勾上

730
00:12:09,033 --> 00:12:10,533
你也可以在月球上收集氧气

731
00:12:10,533 --> 00:12:12,233
这就是你要带一组树叶的原因

732
00:12:12,233 --> 00:12:13,300
随便挖个洞

733
00:12:13,300 --> 00:12:14,166
周围铺满树叶

734
00:12:14,166 --> 00:12:15,333
把收集器放下就行

735
00:12:16,100 --> 00:12:17,833
附近的树叶越多越好

736
00:12:18,433 --> 00:12:19,233
这样一来

737
00:12:19,466 --> 00:12:20,600
你就可以发射了

738
00:12:20,866 --> 00:12:21,833
别忘了什么

739
00:12:58,833 --> 00:12:59,833
控制中心

740
00:12:59,833 --> 00:13:00,866
这里是队长

741
00:13:01,066 --> 00:13:02,066
我们已成功着陆

742
00:13:03,433 --> 00:13:04,533
没时间浪费了

743
00:13:04,833 --> 00:13:07,000
如果有必要可以清怪并把周围点亮

744
00:13:07,066 --> 00:13:08,833
不然就立刻开探矿

745
00:13:08,833 --> 00:13:10,600
顺便找地牢入口

746
00:13:10,666 --> 00:13:12,100
基本上就是地上的一个大洞

747
00:13:12,100 --> 00:13:13,700
你可以看到它底部的砖块

748
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:19,300
目标矿物：钕矿、铝土矿、钛铁矿、铬铁矿、铝矿

749
00:13:19,833 --> 00:13:22,033
这里有大量好东西，足够供养（maybe pick up a better word）主世界

750
00:13:22,466 --> 00:13:25,033
把矿机摆好、配置好，加载区块

751
00:13:25,033 --> 00:13:26,133
然后去打boss

752
00:13:27,700 --> 00:13:28,733
即使你不会飞

753
00:13:28,733 --> 00:13:31,466
你也可以直接穿过地牢，进入boss战场地

754
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:34,700
然后轻松击败boss

755
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:50,433
拿钥匙，开箱子

756
00:13:50,433 --> 00:13:52,866
祈祷出2阶火箭蓝图

757
00:14:02,700 --> 00:14:03,500
呃呃

758
00:14:03,733 --> 00:14:04,666
如果没出蓝图

759
00:14:04,666 --> 00:14:07,100
就继续找地牢刷boss，直到出为止

760
00:14:07,100 --> 00:14:08,200
不会花太多时间的

761
00:14:10,433 --> 00:14:12,433
一旦你对你的收获满意了，就回家吧

762
00:14:12,733 --> 00:14:15,200
顺手在月球 /sethome 也别有心理负担

763
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:17,300
没人会对你指指点点，因为没人知道你干了

764
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:21,800
现在要干的事

765
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:24,133
就是把铝酸盐和铝土矿处理成金红石

766
00:14:25,933 --> 00:14:28,666
把产量拉满非常值得

767
00:14:28,666 --> 00:14:30,733
先把铝土矿研磨成粗碎矿

768
00:14:30,733 --> 00:14:32,966
再用硫酸钠化学浸洗

769
00:14:33,533 --> 00:14:36,900
你还可以把纯净铝土矿做成铝土矿浆，扩展整条产线

770
00:14:36,900 --> 00:14:38,866
并研究一下铝土矿处理产线

771
00:14:39,133 --> 00:14:41,266
这里不展开讲，但建议去查一下

772
00:14:41,333 --> 00:14:44,133
回报离谱，真的离谱

773
00:14:44,733 --> 00:14:46,600
钛铁矿也有类似处理方法

774
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:48,133
区别是用硫酸来产生大量的金红石

775
00:14:48,133 --> 00:14:49,833
（向上合并）

776
00:14:49,833 --> 00:14:52,100
并做一个硫酸循环

777
00:14:52,266 --> 00:14:53,200
但要这等到EV

778
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:54,466
如果你实在缺金红石

779
00:14:54,466 --> 00:14:56,066
也可以让钛铁矿跑完整的

780
00:14:56,066 --> 00:14:58,300
“研磨-洗矿-研磨-离心”线

781
00:14:58,300 --> 00:14:59,433
来获得一点额外的金红石

782
00:14:59,733 --> 00:15:02,000
但最好还是得多挖铝土矿

783
00:15:03,300 --> 00:15:04,533
当你金红石准备充足

784
00:15:04,533 --> 00:15:06,333
就可以开始把它们转化成钛了

785
00:15:07,133 --> 00:15:08,333
任务书解释了怎么做

786
00:15:08,333 --> 00:15:08,866
但总而言之

787
00:15:08,866 --> 00:15:10,833
整条产线是一个大的闭环

788
00:15:10,833 --> 00:15:12,333
唯一的输入是金红石

789
00:15:12,833 --> 00:15:13,533
要启动这产线

790
00:15:13,533 --> 00:15:16,266
你需要在大化反里让金红石和氯、碳反应

791
00:15:16,633 --> 00:15:18,666
把产出的一氧化碳电解处理

792
00:15:18,666 --> 00:15:21,333
四氯化钛和镁一起送进EBF

793
00:15:21,633 --> 00:15:23,300
冷却得到的热钛

794
00:15:23,300 --> 00:15:27,466
再把氯化镁送入化学反应釜与钠反应回收镁

795
00:15:27,466 --> 00:15:31,633
和一些盐；盐再电解就能返还你刚用掉的氯和钠

796
00:15:32,700 --> 00:15:34,400
只需要一点物流

797
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:36,400
只要金红石不断，这产线就能一直跑

798
00:15:39,300 --> 00:15:42,533
而且你会希望它跑很久很久

799
00:15:43,066 --> 00:15:43,866
你做到了

800
00:15:43,900 --> 00:15:45,100
你已经走出前期了

801
00:15:45,300 --> 00:15:47,533
你已经不是新手了

802
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:49,466
新的明天在等待着你

803
00:15:49,666 --> 00:15:51,133
这毕竟是GTNH

804
00:15:51,333 --> 00:15:52,933
学习永远不会停止

805
00:15:53,666 --> 00:15:55,333
HV也有很多事情要做

806
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:56,800
但你现在已经有方法论了

807
00:15:57,266 --> 00:15:59,466
AE已经近在咫尺

808
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:01,633
前提是你能得到足够的钛

809
00:16:02,033 --> 00:16:05,700
希望这期指南给了你足够信息，能真正上手这个整合包

810
00:16:05,933 --> 00:16:06,933
你不会后悔的

811
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:08,333
游戏里见

812
00:16:08,866 --> 00:16:11,233
最后，保持积极，继续加油

